## Revenue Model Analysis

### Project-Based Pricing (35% of firms)

- **Model:** Fixed price per engagement
- **Typical Range:** $5-100K per project
- **Pros:** Simplicity, clarity, cash flow predictability
- **Cons:** Underutilization risk, scope creep
- **Best For:** Strategy, audits, workshops

### Retainer/Monthly Recurring (28% of firms)

- **Model:** Monthly fee for ongoing access/services
- **Typical Range:** $3-15K/month
- **Pros:** Predictable revenue, deeper engagement, relationship building
- **Cons:** Churn risk, upfront commitment required
- **Best For:** Ongoing coaching, strategy support, facilitation

### Hybrid Model (22% of firms)

- **Model:** Retainer + project add-ons
- **Typical Range:** $2-8K/month + $5-50K projects
- **Pros:** Revenue diversification, flexibility, stickiness
- **Cons:** Complexity, pricing transparency challenges
- **Best For:** Mid-size firms serving multiple functions

### Per-Participant Pricing (10% of firms)

- **Model:** Charge per person (training, certification)
- **Typical Range:** $500-5K per participant
- **Pros:** Scales with demand, simple accounting
- **Cons:** Highly commoditized, margin pressure
- **Best For:** Training, workshops, certification

### Membership/Subscription (3% of firms)

- **Model:** Annual or monthly membership for access
- **Typical Range:** $1-10K/year per organization
- **Pros:** Predictable revenue, community building
- **Cons:** Low perceived value, churn risk
- **Best For:** Networks, resource libraries, platforms

### SaaS/Platform-Based (2% of firms)

- **Model:** Annual or usage-based licensing
- **Typical Range:** $5-50K/year depending on scale
- **Pros:** Highest margins (50-70%), unlimited scalability
- **Cons:** High upfront investment, long sales cycle
- **Best For:** Assessments, learning platforms, measurement tools

